# GitHub Copilot Instructions

This file contains instructions for GitHub Copilot when working in this repository.

## Commit Message Guidelines

When creating commit messages, always follow the guidelines in [.github/instructions/copilot-commit-message.md](.github/instructions/copilot-commit-message.md)

**Key rules:**

- Use Conventional Commits format: `<type>(<scope>): <description>`
- Keep first line under 50 characters
- Use imperative mood (add, fix, refactor, not added/fixes/refactoring)
- No period at the end
- Scope is optional but recommended

**Common types:** feat, fix, refactor, perf, docs, style, test, build, ci, chore, revert

Example: `feat(astro): add dark mode support`
